content.en:
An organization should not depend on individual improvisation. If every employee writes prompts alone, quality will remain uneven.

You can build a small library of business prompts. It can cover frequent tasks.

Examples:

- meeting summary;
- customer response;
- procedure sheet;
- action plan;
- complaint analysis;
- plain-language rewriting;
- FAQ preparation;
- checklist creation;
- option comparison;
- project framing note.

Each prompt template should specify context, task, constraints, format, and points to verify.

This library does not replace training. It helps teams adopt shared habits.

## 8. What you should ask AI to do, and not to do

A good prompt does not only say what to do. It also says what to avoid.

You can add simple restrictions.

- “Do not invent numbers.”
- “Do not give legal advice.”
- “Do not cite internal rules that I have not provided.”
- “Do not mention people by name.”
- “If information is missing, say so clearly.”
- “Flag assumptions.”
- “Add a list of points to verify.”

These instructions do not make AI perfect. They improve the frame. They help you spot risky answers faster.

NIST notes that generative AI may produce inaccurate or fabricated content, often referred to as confabulations or hallucinations. Your prompt should therefore include a verification step, especially in professional contexts.

